    "\n",
    "### Question 5: Locate Recipe Cards by Tag and Class\n",
    "\n",
    "Now that youâ€™ve explored the pageâ€™s structure, youâ€™ll focus on finding specific HTML elements that represent **recipe cards**. These are often located within `<article>` tags and associated with specific class names such as `\"recipe-of-the-day\"` (or similar â€” inspect to confirm).\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Instructions\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Inspect the web page and search the HTML for tags related to **recipes**. Look for `article` tags with meaningful `class` attributes (e.g., `class=\"recipe-content-card\"` or similar).\n",
    "2. Use `soup.find_all()` to locate all such `article` tags with the relevant class.\n",
    "3. Assign the result (a list of matching article elements) to a variable named `ans5`.\n",
    "4. Print `ans5` to view the raw HTML snippets retrieved.\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "soup.find_all('...', class_='...')\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Note:** Use `class_` (with underscore) instead of `class`, as `class` is a reserved keyword in Python.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Expected Output** A list of `<article>` elements containing recipe data. It may be empty if there are no recipe of the day."
   ]
